Citation.sTitle: Temperature and Pressure Dependence of the Volumetric Properties of Binary Liquid Mixtures Containing Dihaloalkanes
Citation.sAbstract: Densities of ethyl acetate + dibromomethane, + bromochloromethane, + 1,2- dichloroethane, or + 1-bromo-2-chloroethane binary mixtures were measured at 288.15, 298.15, and 308.15K over the entire composition range. Thermal expansion coefficients and excess molar volumes were calculated. Moreover, densities at 298.15K at pressures up to 200 bar were determined for the same mixtures. Isothermal compressibilities of the pure liquids and their mixtures were obtained. The excess molar volumes are positive, and the excess isothermal compressibilities are negative for all the studied mixtures.
